The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) recommends that British nationals that wish to leave North Macedonia contact their travel operator to make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
This is in response to the ongoing coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic and in line with various controls and restrictions imposed by the authorities of North Macedonia. British nationals in North Macedonia should follow the advice of the authorities of North Macedonia.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
